<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="max" id="max">max</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntaxe :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;algorithm&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">const</span> T<span class="sy3">&amp;</span> max<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">const</span> T<span class="sy3">&amp;</span> x, <span class="kw4">const</span> T<span class="sy3">&amp;</span> y <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
    <span class="kw4">const</span> T<span class="sy3">&amp;</span> max<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">const</span> T<span class="sy3">&amp;</span> x, <span class="kw4">const</span> T<span class="sy3">&amp;</span> y, BinPred p <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
La fonction max() retourne le plus grand des deux arguments x et y, comparés par l&#039;opérateur &lt;.
</p>

<p>
Si le prédicat binaire p est fourni, il sera utilisé à la place de l&#039;opérateur &lt; pour comparer les deux éléments.
</p>

<p>
Le code suivant présente différents exemples d&#039;utilisation de la fonction max() :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">   <span class="kw3">cout</span> <span class="sy1">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;Max de 1 et 9999 est &quot;</span> <span class="sy1">&lt;&lt;</span> max<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="nu0">1</span>, <span class="nu0">9999</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="sy1">&lt;&lt;</span> endl<span class="sy4">;</span>
   <span class="kw3">cout</span> <span class="sy1">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;Max de 'a' et'b' est &quot;</span> <span class="sy1">&lt;&lt;</span> max<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="st0">'a'</span>, <span class="st0">'b'</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="sy1">&lt;&lt;</span> endl<span class="sy4">;</span>
   <span class="kw3">cout</span> <span class="sy1">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;Max de 3.14159 et2.71828 est &quot;</span> <span class="sy1">&lt;&lt;</span> max<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="nu16">3.14159</span>, <span class="nu16">2.71828</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="sy1">&lt;&lt;</span> endl<span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
Ces lignes donneront le résultat suivant :
</p>
<pre class="code">
   Max de 1 et 9999 est 9999
   Max de 'a' et 'b' est b
   Max de 3.14159 et 2.71828 est 3.14159</pre>
<p>
